UML:Package.name: 01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:TaggedValue.value: Uploading of AAL services will be allowed for users that were approved to play service providers roles - Service providers will be able to provide all kinds of services - Uploaded service will be associated with a group and/or users (as selected by user during uploading process) - Developers who wish to upload software from depot server or depot client (by using artifact's meta data & additional meta data from developer), will play the role of service provider for this service and will be allowed to upload the service. In this case uStore will save link to the artifact from specific develop depot and can also save specific user/password for this (if it's not same as an uStore user) - The permission to edit/delete this service will be done based on user+service couple (and may be extended in the future)
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
uStore will exploit dependency analysis and compatibility analysis to avoid that AAL Services are bought twice when, for example, other AAL Services exist
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
Identification mechanism for services. Every service will have ids that identify it, its association to group and version. (Specify details on the ids here)
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

AAL service will contain metadata depending on what are its parts (i.e. for human resources geographic location is required, like country, city, area etc). If the service is mapped to artifact in develop depot, it will include artifact id, and in UI will be presented all the relevant data from develop depot.
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

An approval process for ensuring that resources made available in the uStore are consistent with universAAL architectural policies will exist on the uStore web site 1) For software conformance tools will be implemented in task 3.3 and will be integrated in the uStore 2) For other services, uStore will save a policy that would be checked for every new proposed service (optionally including manual acceptance by administrator)
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
Software components (e.g OSGi Bundle, Android Package, .NET-based) on multiple execution environments (e.g Android, Windows, Symbian and Linux) will be supported
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.10 The uStore must provide a mechism for notifying the user about the ticket status

UML:TaggedValue.value:
The status should include information about:
  • How many times viewed
  • How many appearances in searches
  • If and when selected for implementation
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
AAL service will include software (applications and device drivers), hardware, courses and/or human resources or any combination of them or other AAL services
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.13 The uStore must provide an interface for creating an advanced service ticket

UML:TaggedValue.value:
The uStore should provide an interface for creating an advanced service request ticket.
The interface can be a web page or a tailored program.
The interface should allow for refinement of existing tickets (simple and advanced) The interface should for specification of all the simple ticket elements, and in addition estimation of cost and required development effort.
A free text field for notes should be available.
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
There will be a versioning mechanism for services (preferably similar to one in develop depot)
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

Capability-requirement model will be used: every service will provide its requirements and capabilities it provides in a similar way to the described in the following specifications: - JSR-124 http://jcp.org/aboutJava/communityprocess/final/jsr124/ - OSGi Bundle repository http://www.osgi.org/download/rfc-0112_BundleRepository.pdf There may be additional mechanisms to group few services together to answer user's request (more details needed here)
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.14 The uStore should allow for advertisements based on user profile

UML:TaggedValue.value: The uStore should allow for "push" of advertisements. The advertisements can be adjusted to the user's interests.
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.12 The uStore must provide an easy to use interface to create a service request ticket

UML:TaggedValue.value:
The uStore should provide an interface, e.g. web page where a registered user easily can add a new request for a service. This will create a new ticket.
The ticket should hold information about service category, requester, date/time, service details (text, picture, voice recording).
It should be possible to add requester contact information (to elaborate on details).
A receipt should be sent to the requester on request submission.
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.16 The uStore must notify the service requester/notification subscriber when service becomes available

UML:TaggedValue.value:
uStore must notify the end user via the preferred channel when:
  • new services in the defined area of interest becomes available
  • the ticket request has been fulfilled (completed)
  • the ticket request receives a responder that estimates a delivery date and price
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.15 The uStore should provide a mechanism for subcribing to ticket requests

UML:TaggedValue.value: A registered user (end user, developer, provider roles) should be able to subscribe to a selected set (cateogory/keywords) of ticket requests
01. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:ClassifierRole.name: 1.11 The uStore must provide a mechnism for viewing statistics about ticket request and their status

UML:TaggedValue.value: The statistics should include information about requester, category of service, response time, development time and developer/provider information
01. Service providers will offer AAL services
